track_notes:
From the junction of I-10 and Trans-Mountain road in West El Paso, go east on Trans-Mountain road over the peak at Smugglers Pass (5280 ft). As you start down the east side, enter the parking lot on the right. Stop and pay the park fee at the pay station on the west side of the parking lot. The trail begins just beyond the pay station on the right side.

Follow the trail up the canyon. At 0.45 miles, the main trail keeps right. DO NOT follow the wash up. At 0.5 miles the trail will zig-zag up the hillside covered in red rhyolite rock to the ridgeline. On the ridgeline at 0.80 miles, turn left and follow the trail up toward the Elephants Trunk at N31.86502 - W106.49520. Before reaching the trunk, follow the main trail to the left and continue up the narrowing canyon.

You will reach another fork as you top out in the canyon. Take the left fork and continue up between the towers. South Franklin Mountain has two nearly equal summits, with a shallow saddle between them.
